    prefix: '25e4b5de',
    text: `You have set a 60,000-triangle budget per character and 2048x2048 texture cap for a multiplayer brawler in Unreal 5 targeting PS5, Series S, and PC. The lead character artist argues the protagonist needs 90,000 triangles and 4096 textures because it is centre-screen in the lobby and marketing. They are correct about the visual quality difference. But Series S drops below 60fps in a 4-player lobby at current budgets -- adding 30,000 triangles to one character (which appears on both teams) adds 60,000 triangles to the worst case. You profile: the 4-player lobby on Series S currently runs at 62fps with 240,000 character triangles total. Adding 60,000 drops it to 54fps. Three compromise approaches: (A) grant the protagonist 90,000 at LOD0 but force LOD1 to kick in at 8 metres (closer than the standard 15 metres), so gameplay never sees LOD0 -- only the lobby does; (B) keep 60,000 triangles but grant a 4096 texture and a unique shader with higher-fidelity subsurface scattering and micro-detail normal maps -- visually richer without the geometry cost; (C) grant 75,000 triangles (halfway) and reduce the other 7 characters to 55,000 to keep the total budget flat -- the other characters lose visual fidelity to fund the protagonist. Choose one. Rule out one and state the specific platform or scenario where it fails. For your choice, state how you verify the Series S framerate holds before the build ships.`
